name: Reimu
desc: The Hakurei shrine maiden. Her main job is to exterminate youkai, which makes her quite moody.

name: Marisa
desc: A human magician living in the forest. Friendly and curious, but also a thief and a hoarder.

name: Kasen
desc: A hermit from the mountain. She acts as a mentor to Reimu and often lectures her. Holds a secret below her wisdom.

name: Kasen
desc: A hermit from the mountain. She acts as a mentor to Reimu and often lectures her. Holds a secret below her wisdom.

name: Remilia
desc: The owner of the SDM. She acts refined, but is actually quite childish. Her status makes her feared by many.

name: Aunn
desc: A komainu statue who came to life. She is pure-hearted and dutifully guards temples and shrines.

name: Tokiko
desc: A bird youkai who mostly minds her own business. Likes reading.

name: Letty
desc: A yuki-onna who is only active during the winter. Has a chill and calm demeanour, but doesn't really understand humans.

name: Rumia
desc: The youkai of darkness. Eats humans, but doesn't bother hunting them. Not the brightest.

name: Kokoro
desc: A menreiki who loves to perform Noh. She is very emotional and expresses herself through her masks.

name: Suika
desc: An oni who squats in Hakurei Shrine. Her physical strength is almost unmatched.

name: Rinnosuke
desc: The owner of Kourindou, a curio shop. Tries to be a purveyor of interesting curios, but often falls short in analysis.

name: Rinnosuke
desc: The owner of Kourindou, a curio shop. Tries to be a purveyor of interesting curios, but often falls short in analysis.

name: Kosuzu
desc: The shopgirl who oversees the shop "Suzunaan". She has a relatively unhealthy obsession with youma scrolls.

name: Kosuzu
desc: The shopgirl who oversees the shop "Suzunaan". She has a relatively unhealthy obsession with youma scrolls.

name: Akyuu
desc: The Child of Miare, she has the ability to never forget a single thing. Currently being kept alive by pure bullshit energy.

name: Wriggle
desc: An insect youkai who is a leader of bugs in Gensokyo. She gets mad when you badmouth them.

name: Mystia
desc: A night sparrow who loves to sing. Also runs an izakaya and scams people using night blindness.

name: Kagerou
desc: A werewolf who is a member of the Grassroots Youkai Network. Usually more friendly and reasonable when not acting up.

name: Sunny
desc: One of the three Fairies of Light. She is confident and acts as their leader.

name: Luna
desc: One of the three Fairies of Light. Calmer than other fairies, but also very clumsy.

name: Star
desc: One of the three Fairies of Light. Often lets the other two do all the work.

name: Cirno
desc: An ice fairy living on Misty Lake. Stronger than other fairies, so she’s quite full of herself.

name: Daiyousei
desc:
A fairy friend of Cirno's. Playful and mischievous, but a bit 
shyer than other fairies.

name: Seiran
desc: A deserter from the Lunar Capital. She seems to love her new home on Earth. Makes a mean mochi.

name: Ringo
desc: A deserter from the Lunar Capital. Gains strength from eating dango, but she also owns a dango stand.

name: Tewi
desc: The White Rabbit of Inaba. Insanely lucky and known to spread luck blessings around.

name: Reisen
desc: A rabbit from the moon whose eyes can send enemies into a frenzy. She sells medicine in the Human Village under the orders of Eirin.

name: SigmaRaven
desc: hes going to murder me if i save with lt open again

name: Mokou
desc: Scion of the Fujiwara clan, Mokou is cursed with immortality and revives whenever she dies. Rivals with Kaguya.

name: Kaguya
desc: A princess from the Lunarian Kingdom on the Moon, Kaguya is a fairly curious person and shares a rivalry with Mokou.

name: Kogasa
desc: A karakasa obake whose main goal in life is to scare as many people as possible. Also is a great blacksmith.

name: Kogasa
desc: A karakasa obake whose main goal in life is to scare as many people as possible. Also is a great blacksmith.

name: Mima
desc: Marisa's mentor. She's a vengeful spirit who's usually found haunting Hakurei Shrine. Nowadays, she seems to be wandering Gensokyo...

name: Sakuya
desc: Head maid of the Scarlet Devil Mansion. A witty, responsible, and sometimes composed maid. Tends to be a little silly otherwise.

name: Alice
desc: A dollmaking magician who resides in the Forest of Magic. She is a reticient but helpful person who specializes in puppetry.

name: Koakuma
desc: A servant of the Scarlet Devil Mansion. She's mostly found helping out Patchouli in her library.

name: Narumi
desc: A jizo who was brought out by the Four Seasons Incident. Quite the introvert.

name: Youmu
desc: The gardener of Hakugyoukurou. She's a talented swordswoman and a loyal servant but has the tendency to be a bit airheaded at times.

name: Yuyuko
desc: The mistress of Hakugyoukuro. She capable of making almost anybody die. However, she usually spends her days chowing down on food and relaxing.

name: Patchouli
desc: A magician living in the Scarlet Devil Mansion. She is a powerful magician with a large library, but she is also very frail and unlucky.

name: Keine
desc: A were-hakutaku acting as the guardian of the Human Village. Very kind, but do not get on her bad side

name: Eirin
desc: A medical mastermind god from the Moon, Eirin is an expert pharmacist and runs Eientei with Kaguya. She has existed for millenia.

name: Miki
desc: A gallavanting human who is backed by immense faith in an Arthurian legends.

name: Konami
desc: A lazy youkai who likes to take long walks down the canal with her friends.

name: Kabin
desc: A firebrand amateur incident solver. She hasn't solved any incidents.

name: Yae
desc: A deceptive kitsune who enjoys playing pranks on her fellow youkai.

name: Amane
desc: A youkai who got herself trapped under a pile of scrap metal that she now lugs around as armor.

name: Tomomi
desc: A marauding youkai who pretends to be a raider along the Human Village canals. Mostly just a nuisance.

name: Yuna
desc: A hunter from the Human Village who is relatively adept at a bow, but still angers youkai when she hits them with strays.

name: Yuika
desc: A graverobbing youkai who is on the lam for her crimes in various cemetaries. Her greatest fear is running into the Yamaxanadu.

name: Miu
desc: A fledging swordswoman who wanders around, challenging fairies. It is said that she is an urban legend amongst the fairies at Misty Lake.

name: Akane
desc: A youkai nun hailing from Myouren Temple who follows her vows very loosely. Mostly there for the free food.

name: Haruka
desc: A youkai of darkness who seems to have a particular rivalry with Rumia.

name: Kana
desc: A yamawaro mercenary who has been lost in the Bamboo Forest for a week.

name: Meiko
desc: A moon rabbit fugitive who seeks out a living by selling bodyguard services.

name: Hanae
desc: A tsukumogami created from the vengeful spirit of an Outside World mall katana.

name: Yoshino
desc: A courier for Eientei. Known for her swiftness in delivering goods.

name: Sena
desc: A youkai hunter who crusades against the creeping threat of youkai interference on humans.

name: Yomi
desc: A woodcutting youkai residing in the Forest of Magic. Has a reputation for being "cool". Kasuka's friend.

name: Kasuka
desc: A hunter youkai residing in the Forest of Magic. Has a reputation for being "cute". Yomi's friend.

name: Reiko
desc: A conniving tanuki who swindles foolish fairies out of their petty goods.

name: Sen
desc: A battle maniac who throws herself into the thick of battle with no concern for her own life.

name: Karin
desc: A studious human trying to become a magician. Tends to be a bit clumsy.

name: Han-eul
desc: A dokkaebi from Korea who has transmigrated to Gensokyo. A fickle creature prone to helping or harming people.

name: Taiga
desc: A werewolf disciple of Myouren Temple who idolizes Shou Toramaru. Attempts to fight like a tiger.

name: Marple
desc: A shrewd but ancient youkai who simply does as she pleases. However, she's not exactly as strong as other older youkai to enforce her will on others.

name: Pomona
desc: A great fairy who resides near the Border of Life & Death. She's a harvest fairy, but it's hard to grow crops in such a desolate area.

name: Sayuri
desc: An earnest white wolf tengu who was assigned to help find stories for a tengu newspaper.
